LESS(1)                          User Commands                         LESS(1)

NAME
       less - opposite of more

SYNOPSIS
       less [options] [file ...]

DESCRIPTION
       less  is  a  program  similar  to more, but it allows backward
       movement in the file as well as forward movement.  Also, less
       does  not  have  to  read  the  entire  input file before starting,
       so with large input files it starts up faster than text editors.

OPTIONS
       -c     repaint screen from top instead of scrolling

       -e     quit at second end-of-file

       -E     quit at first end-of-file

       -f     force open non-regular files

       -g     highlight only last search match

       -G     don't highlight search matches

       -i, --ignore-case
              ignore case in searches

       -I, --IGNORE-CASE
              ignore case even when pattern has uppercase

       -J, --status-column
              display a status column

       -m     use a medium prompt (filename + percentage)

       -M     use a long prompt (filename + lines + percentage)

       -N, --line-numbers
              show line numbers

       -q, --quiet, --silent
              quiet (no bell)

       -Q, --QUIET, --SILENT
              very quiet

       -r, --raw-control-chars
              raw control characters

       -R, --RAW-CONTROL-CHARS
              output ANSI color escape sequences in raw form

       -s, --squeeze-blank-lines
              squeeze consecutive blank lines

       -S, --chop-long-lines
              chop (truncate) long lines rather than wrapping

       -V, --version
              display version information and exit

       -x, --tabs=n
              set tab stops (default 8)

       -X, --no-init
              don't send termcap initialization and deinitialization
              strings

       -z, --window=n
              set window size; if negative, window is that many lines
              less than screen height

       -~, --tilde
              don't display tildes after end-of-file

       -#, --shift=n
              horizontal scroll amount

       --use-color
              enable colored text

       --help display this help and exit

       +command
              initial command (e.g., +G go to end, +/pattern search,
              +N go to line N)

INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
       SPACE, f, PgDn
              forward one window

       b, PgUp
              backward one window

       RETURN, e, j, Down
              forward one line

       y, k, Up
              backward one line

       d      forward half window

       u      backward half window

       g, <, Home
              go to beginning of file (or line N)

       G, >, End
              go to end of file (or line N)

       Np or N%
              go to N percent into file

       /pattern
              search forward for pattern

       ?pattern
              search backward for pattern

       n      repeat previous search

       N      repeat previous search in reverse direction

       m<letter>
              set a mark at the current position

       '<letter>
              go to a previously set mark

       -<flag>
              toggle a command-line option at runtime

       =      display file information

       :n     examine the next file

       :p     examine the previous file

       :e file
              examine a new file

       q, :q, Q
              quit

       h, H   display help

       r, R   repaint screen

       Right  scroll right

       Left   scroll left

ENVIRONMENT
       LESS   Default options for less.

